<br>
I cant justify it&quot;<br>
<br>
Can you not justify it because more evade would make us too defensive, or you can't justify it because we don't need more defense?<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if I can agree that evade two would be unjustifiable. Not only does evade one hardly ever kick in, but we die pretty quickly our there anyways, dispite our armor.<br>
<br>
When Mythic gave us evade 1, I believe they felt that would bring us up to a comparible rate of reinforced + evade 3. However, what they don't understand, is evade one is pretty much null and void, even with buffs and the dodger RA. In fact, if you want to count evade in your typical fight, you must have a good level of dodger and buffs in order to really consider yourself to have evade (I think someone said dodger 3 with max buffs makes it so you actually evade once per 2-3 battles, which is what I believe mythic originally had intended). They over-estimated evade 1, from what I conduct. I don't enjoy the aspect of &quot;having&quot; to invest RAs into a skill that is suppose to work on its own, nor do I feel it's fair. These are suppose to be bonus points, not make-up-for-lack-of-design points. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
