<br>
One cool reason for Evade2 to be given for mercs is our special ability is a random (like everything that fires off a merc) and defensive one instead of a offensive one (except in 1v1 where it could be considered offensive)<br>
<br>
If chain+E1= Reinforced+E3=Stud+E3 that's an OK philosophy I guess.<br>
<br>
But 'Zerk gives a full 50% (averaged out of course) extra damage (applied to everything- just like polearm style damage is and CDWLA style damage isnt) <br>
<br>
And TW gives a full 50% extra damage, modified by buffs and dealing energy damage instead of 'melee' (eg, Slash, which is likely to be a primary resist of all targets)<br>
<br>
In their patch notes Mythic almost says that it's the improvement in special abilities (or jut leaving Zerk7 as it is) that will help a Light Tank make up for their somewhat lack of damage. <br>
<br>
^ I think I read that they revised them somewhere on these boards, in the BM thread, in order to change their stance on the 'Zerk being able to kill all big tanks', because LA players were grabbing at that like a burning rope <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway- seeing as how our new 7 minute timer special ability which is supposed to raise us up to the standard of a heavy tank and make it so that Mythics notes on armsman+merc&gt;Armsman+armsman can be proven true...<br>
<br>
is a defensive ability that can get resisted  and lasts for llike 30 seconds...<br>
<br>
I still think we're going to have a lot more trouble fighting a red-con enemy alongside an armsman than two armsmen will be, DT or no. I know I'd rather have had my damage boosted by 50% for the fight than give my enemy a 35% to fumble, affected by resists.<br>
<br>
If you look at it another way, 15% evade+19%absorb is 2% better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    than 27%absorb and 5%evade<br>
