<br>
Using dragonfang for the win shouldn't (shouldn't, but you never know with mythic) be an issue. Minstrels get evade 2 and can spec thrust, and get chain just like us, so why forbid it from us? It's also not fair to limit us that way, just because thrust has some ultra-strong level 50 style. I'm slash, and i'm still getting no evade because something a thrust merc could have? I know Mythic works in a strange, probably unidentifiable way, but i'm confadent they have enough basic logic to realized thrusts potential to us is still lackluster and one level 50 style is not going to overpower us (fact, i believe going thrust gimps mercs since they're so evade based and have no good anytime).<br>
<br>
What I think people who do not want evade 2 beleive, is that, if we do what we are suppose to (deal good damage quickly), that it will counter-balance our need for more defense. Taking something down fast would provide us with the best kind of defense, after all. What I don't believe people realize is that vision of the merc cannot come to pass. There is no way we could be allowed to kill so quickly that evade 2 would be considered useless. Now with us being paired and an arms, giving us more damage potential (to the point where evade 2 does nothing) also poses a threat - why be a frontloading arms when the merc next to you hits for more damage anyways (over a little bit of time), and I only last a few hits longer? We would be stepping on our plate-brothers toes, something I don't want to do.<br>
<br>
If this was my perfect little world and I had control over everything, i'd have it set so we did advance-spec line damage with evade 2. I see that as being perfect, not too strong, not too weak.<br>
<br>
But, it's not. And i'm sure everyone and their mother will complain because of the not-so-useless-now mercenary can actually kill a caster on his own (assuming no heals). <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
